default4.8 Eligibility 
defaultto use 
defaultCommunity Transport is often misunderstood and an 
defaultenigma 
default to
default many people. This is important when we realise that visitors from the city - to attractions; walking etc - are an important rural economic benefit. More use of these buses by 
defaultvisitors to the area 
defaultto return to their cars/stations etc would add to revenue and open access to the countryside. Dales Bus 
defaultseem
default to have done a lot to provide such services but knowledge of their exist
defaulte
defaultnce remains thin.
default&#xa0;
default4.9 
defaultLegislation is required to simplify the regulation of small passenger carrying vehicles with eight or 
defaultfewer
default passenger seats which currently may be operated as part of a voluntary car sharing agreement, under Restricted PSV O-licences issued by the Traffic Commissioners or under taxi/private hire vehicle licenses (issued by local authorities).
default&#xa0;
default4.10 
defaultThe example of the Royal Mail in allowing passengers to share some of the spare capacity on suitably converted mail vans is unfortunately unlikely to be repeated soon, but the principle of hybrid vehicles carrying goods and passengers has the potential to be developed 
default&#xa0;
default4.11 
defaultThe uncertainty surrounding the future of BSOG should be addressed. A grant  based on fuel used (a proxy for mileage) would assist rural transport operators more than one based on patronage, which will by definition be low in isolated communities.
default&#xa0;
